By Gami Tadanyigbe  Kuje (FCT) –   A 29-year-old mechanic, Kayode Olusola, on Tuesday was arraigned in a Kuje Upper Area Court, charged with stealing of electrical cables, valued at N200,000, from a building site. Olusola, who resides at Anguwan Gade area in Kuje, was charged with criminal trespass and theft, but pleaded not guilty to the charges. The prosecutor, Doris Okoroba, told the court that the case was reported by one Ishaku Yakuba, at the Kuje police station on Sept. 3. Okoroba said that the accused entered the building site belonging to the complainant and stole electrical cables valued at N200,000. She said that Olusola tried to sell the stolen cables to a buyer at the Tipper Garage when he was caught and handed over to the police. The prosecutor said the offences contravened Section 312 and 187 of the penal code. The presiding judge, Malam Abdullahi Abdulkareem, granted bail to the accused in the sum of N100, 000 with one surety in like sum. Abdulkareem said that the surety must reside within the jurisdiction of the Court. The case was adjourned until Oct. 4 for mention. (NAN)